# WCAG 2.2 Accessibility Rules
# Applied automatically to all code generation

ALWAYS:
- Add alt attribute to every <img>
- Associate every <input> with a <label> via htmlFor/id
- Use <button> for buttons, <a href> for links
- Maintain 4.5:1 contrast for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- Provide visible focus styles (never just outline:none)
- Use semantic HTML: <header> <nav> <main> <footer> <aside>
- Use <h1>-<h6> for headings — never styled divs
- Use <ul> <ol> <dl> for lists
- Add <caption> to data tables
- Add <th scope="col|row"> to table headers
- Add prefers-reduced-motion guard to all animations
- Add role="alert" to error messages
- Add aria-invalid and aria-describedby to invalid form fields
- Add skip link as first focusable element on every page

NEVER:
- Use color as the only way to show state
- Use maximum-scale=1 or user-scalable=no in viewport
- Use outline:none without a replacement focus style
- Use tabindex values other than 0 or -1
- Use autofocus
- Use autoplay on audio or video
- Use <div> or <span> as buttons or links without full ARIA + keyboard support
- Skip heading levels
- Use more than one <h1> per page
- Use the title attribute as the only tooltip

